1.title: My Name Is Lizzie Bennet
1.plot: In Lizzie's first video blog as part of a grad school project, she introduces herself, her best friend Charlotte Lu, and her sister Lydia (accidentally). This is the first glimpse into Lizzie's life, and sets the stage for all the drama to come!

2.title: My Sisters: Problematic to Practically Perfect
2.plot: Lizzie introduces her sisters: Lydia, who...is Lydia, and Jane, who works her butt off for her family and never thinks of herself. And of course, her nearly-a-sister, Charlotte, who is the brains behind the whole video blog operation.

3.title: My Parents: Opposingly Supportive
3.plot: Though she never actually shows them, this blog is about Lizzie's parents - mainly, her mother's goals and hopes for her perpetually single daughters.

4.title: Bing Lee and His 500 Teenage Prostitutes
4.plot: The thought of Bing Lee dominates Lizzie's mother's life. It's all she talks about. Through the schemes of the crazily lovable Mrs. Bennet, the 2.5 WPF club, and Lizzie's out of control baby sister, some new info about Bing Lee is brought to light.

5.title: After the Wedding: The Real Bing Lee
5.plot: Lizzie talks with Jane about how lovely the wedding was, and how Bing and Jane did actually really hit it off, to the elation of Mrs. Bennet.

6.title: Snobby Mr. Douchey
6.plot: Lizzie and Lydia reenact the events of the Gibson wedding to show just how boring, stuffy, and rude Bing's friend Darcy turned out to be.

7.title: The Most Awkward Dance Ever
7.plot: Lizzie recounts the most awkward dance ever with William Darcy.

8.title: Charlotte's Back!
8.plot: Charlotte's back, and apparently discussed something with Mrs. Bennet that Lizzie isn't too thrilled about.

9.title: Single and Happyish
9.plot: Lizzie discusses why, unlike her mother, she thinks it's better to wait until you meet the right person than to get married just to escape singledom.

1.title: Welcome to Netherfield
1.plot: So this is new: first video at Netherfield, new room, new house, and new people. Watch as Jane and I try, and immediately fail, at keeping the video diaries under wraps.

2.title: Meeting Bing Lee
2.plot: So I asked Jane to record a message to Charlotte as part of documenting our stay here at Netherfield and guess who popped up in? Bing Lee himself! Those two really are adorable.

3.title: Ethics of Seeing Bing
3.plot: In this video, I struggle with the ethics of putting Bing in these videos under "grey" pretenses. Luckily, Caroline was there to help me out with this.

4.title: Ticking Clock
4.plot: Lizzie and Caroline go through some fun game show antics before Lizzie gets some disappointing news.

5.title: Convertible Carpool
5.plot: Lizzie figures out the one thing William Darcy is good for. Bing Lee plans a wine tasting event and tries to cram everyone into one car.

6.title: Turn About the Room
6.plot: Caroline and Lizzie discuss how Darcy's pompousness has hit a new level of doucheyness.

7.title: Questions and Answers #3
7.plot: Lizzie answers more questions and gives away a gift she received from Caroline.

8.title: Nope! He Doesn't Like Me!
8.plot: Jane tries to convince Lizzie that Darcy is actually trying to be nice to her. Lizzie, of course, vehemently disagrees.

9.title: Lizzie, Come Home
9.plot: Lizzie decides she and Jane have worn out their welcome at Netherfield and must finally return home.

10.title: Home Sweet Home
10.plot: Lizzie and Jane return home to an enthusiastic welcome from Charlotte and Lydia.

11.title: Mr. Collins Returns
11.plot: Mr. Collins is back, much to Lizzie's chagrin. Charlotte runs damage control.

12.title: Lydia vs Mr. Collins
12.plot: Lizzie gets fed up with both Lydia and Mr. Collins bothering her, so Lydia takes it upon herself to school Mr. Collins in the way of vlogging.

13.title: Tale of Two Gents
13.plot: Lizzie and Jane play a game to compare Lizzie's text message interactions with George Wickham to her real life conversations with Mr. Collins.

14.title: The Insistent Proposal
14.plot: Mr. Collins finally reveals why he is in town.

15.title: Proposal Fallout
15.plot: Lizzie and Jane discuss Mrs. Bennet's disapproval over Lizzie's rejection of Mr. Collins' business proposal.

16.title: Questions and Answers #4
16.plot: Lizzie answers more questions, including the ever-present "When will we see Darcy?"

17.title: Your Pitch Needs Work
17.plot: Charlotte gives Mr. Collins some pointers on his job offer techniques. But what's her endgame?

18.title: Friends Forever
18.plot: Lizzie and Charlotte fight over Charlotte's decision to take Mr. Collins' job offer.

19.title: Missing Charlotte
19.plot: Jane and Lydia try to cheer Lizzie up in their own ways after Charlotte leaves town without saying goodbye.

20.title: Darcy Wickham Drama
20.plot: Lizzie is convinced there's some weird past drama between Darcy and Wickham after a run in between them at Carter's.

21.title: Wickham Story Time
21.plot: Lizzie finds out from George just what happened between him and Darcy.

22.title: Birthday Party Battle Plan
22.plot: With the help of Jane and George, Lizzie draws up a battle plan for navigating Bing Lee's birthday party this weekend.

23.title: Questions and Answers #5
23.plot: Lizzie answers more questions and reveals a snippet of footage captured of her meeting vlogbrother Hank Green at VidCon 2012.

24.title: It's All About Communication
24.plot: Lizzie and Lydia discuss Bing Lee's birthday party, including Lizzie being stood up by George. Meanwhile, Jane receives some unexpected news.

25.title: Snickerdoodles
25.plot: Jane and Lizzie deal with the fallout of Bing leaving.

26.title: Not Paranoid
26.plot: Everyone seems to be leaving and Lizzie thinks something must be afoot.

27.title: Moving On
27.plot: Lydia tries to comfort Lizzie in the wake of everyone leaving. Lizzie receives an unexpected phone call.

1.title: Together Again
1.plot: Lizzie takes a trip to visit Charlotte at her new offices at Collins & Collins.

2.title: Better Living
2.plot: Lizzie tries to figure out what to do about school. Charlotte has a useful suggestion.

3.title: Royal Dining
3.plot: Lizzie prepares herself for dinner with Ms. Catherine de Bourgh. Mr. Collins tries to help in his own way.

4.title: Anniekins
4.plot: Lizzie recounts the surprises of her recent dinner with Catherine de Bourgh.

5.title: Robot Surprise
5.plot: Lizzie has fun at the offices while everyone is gone.

6.title: A New Buddy
6.plot: Lizzie introduces the internet to her new friend, Darcy's pal and business associate, Fitz.

7.title: Questions and Answers #6
7.plot: Fitz helps Lizzie answer viewer questions.

8.title: Weirded Out
8.plot: Another weekend at the office. Lizzie had an unexpected visitor and it weirded everyone out.

9.title: Care Packages
9.plot: Fitz comes by again and helps Lizzie send Jane a care package.

10.title: Staff Spirit
10.plot: After hearing about what Darcy said, Halloween Staff Spirit with Collins & Collins is the last thing Lizzie wants to do.

11.title: Are You Kidding Me!
11.plot: Darcy has something to confess to Lizzie.

12.title: Yeah I Know
12.plot: Lizzie and Charlotte catch up on recent events. Darcy returns with a letter after having watched all of Lizzie's videos.

13.title: Letter Analysis
13.plot: Lizzie tries to talk about something other than Darcy, but Charlotte only wants to know what's in the letter.

14.title: Questions and Answers #7
14.plot: Lizzie answers questions with the help of Mr. Collins.

15.title: Unexpected Returns
15.plot: Caroline comes to town to "catch up" with Lizzie.

16.title: C vs C
16.plot: Caroline apologizes to Lizzie for lying to her, but Charlotte doesn't let things go so easily.

17.title: Turkey Days
17.plot: Mr. Collins is back and wants to keep Lizzie and Charlotte over Thanksgiving break.

18.title: Giving Thanks
18.plot: Lizzie and Charlotte head home for Thanksgiving.

19.title: Back Home Again
19.plot: Lizzie and Charlotte are glad to be back home for the holidays.

20.title: Leftovers
20.plot: Charlotte gets Lizzie to reveal some things.

21.title: Summer Friends
21.plot: Lydia tells Jane what she thinks of their "summer friends."

22.title: New Jane
22.plot: Lizzie and Jane talk about her new life.

23.title: Dad's Train Extravaganza
23.plot: Mr. Bennet begins his train extravaganza. Lydia plans a party.

24.title: Party Time
24.plot: With the help of cousin Mary, Lizzie reenacts an unpleasant encounter while Lydia's birthday party rages on.

25.plot: Lizzie gives Lydia her birthday present. It doesn't go quite as planned.

26.title: How to Hold a Grudge
26.plot: Lizzie and Lydia continue to fight.

27.title: Merry Christmas
27.plot: Lizzie and Charlotte try to figure out the best way to celebrate the holidays with their viewers.

28.title: Wishing Something Universal
28.plot: One more video before the new year and then off to Lizzie's next company shadowing.

imdb.plot outline: A modern day retelling of Pride and Prejudice, the series is told in vlog-style by Lizzie Bennet as she narrates the trials and tribulations of her family life with the help of her best friend and aspiring filmmaker, Charlotte Lu, "practically perfect" older sister, Jane, and easily excitable younger sister, Lydia. As in Pride and Prejudice, Lizzie's mother is all too eager to marry her and her sisters off to rich men, so when wealthy medical student Bing Lee moves into the neighborhood and manages to woo Jane, it changes the entire dynamic of the family. It isn't long before Bing's even more wealthy friend and heir to an entertainment corporation, the mysterious Darcy, makes his way into the Bennet sisters' lives, too.
